Every 11 years, the sun undergoes a solar maximum. A solar maximum is a time during the sun's solar cycle when the number of sunspots and general solar activity should increase. During this time, the sun usually hurls out more solar flares and coronal mass ejections (CMEs). This has left researchers worried as they begin discussing the possible causes of this unusual occurrence.
